node.text:
A night photoshoot with @michellevonkalben is always worth it☺️ I had seen one image taken in this cave in daylight but I am always drawn a bit more towards mystical and dreamy feeling with my photos. Night worked perfectly here.
-
Technically these shoots are a bit more challenging since I always shoot everything seperate. Like this I can customize the look however I want in PS. For this I shot the background, cave without lanterns, cave with lanterns but without Michelle, lighthouse and cave with lanterns and Michelle. I shot everything as HDR and then combined together in Photoshop afterwards👍🏻

May be an image of castle and outdoors.

node.text:
Here it is. The shot and edit I wanted to be able to photograph and create from Mont Saint Michel. 🏰
-
I visited this place already back in 2018 and I knew when I’d eventually return, I’d want to find some new angles. It’s very hard to find elevated areas there and the perspective I had in mind had to be higher.
-
We woke up early in the morning to scout the nearby areas. Google Maps showed 10kms to an area that seemed to be a bit higher than most of the land.
-
We eventually found a steep ish road and the angle at the top was EXACTLY what I had hoped for. Maybe the foreground could’ve been a bit more interesting but I was more than happy with it. 100-500mm came in handy with this edit.
-
This is why I love photography and editing; you get to plan something you have in your mind and if everything goes well you can bring those ideas into fruition.
